<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Brazil-SexEd     07-16 0192</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Brazil-Sex Ed,0196</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teachers Fired for Exposing Themselves to Pupils</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note Contents</NOTE>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two female teachers were fired
after partially undressing in front of their 1st and 2nd grade
pupils as part of a sex education class, a city education
administrator said.
   ``The teachers were fired because the concensus here was that
they went overboard in their sex education demonstration,'' Osvaldo
Feliz Oliveira, the administrator who dismissed the teachers, said
Friday. ``It's one thing for kids to see this kind of thing on TV
and another to see it in the classroom.''
   He said the teachers were fired Wednesday after an inquiry
determined that they showed parts of their bodies to the pupils
during the class on April 23. He identified the teachers as Maria
Calabressi Tresoldi, 29; and Maria Vicente Barbosa, 24.
   Another teacher who observed the sex education class and the
parents of some pupils were among 20 people who testified at the
administrative inquiry in the town of Osorio, 990 miles southwest
of Rio de Janeiro.
   The administrator said the incident prompted parents of some
pupils to transfer them to another school.
</TEXT>
