<FILEID>AP-NR-07-16-88 0839EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Iran-Iraq     07-16 0086</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Iran-Iraq,0093</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Iraq Raids Iranian Oil Pumping Station</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iraq said its warplanes today raided two
Iranian oil pumping stations near the southern city of Dezful.
   No casualties were reported.
   The official Iraqi News Agency, monitored in Cyprus, said the
raids were ``destructive and effective,'' but it did not elaborate.
   Iran did not comment on the Iraqi claims. The report could not
be indepedently confirmed.
   Iraq's raids are aimed at destroying Iran's oil lifeline, which
finances the nearly 8-year-old war with Iraq.
</TEXT>
