<1ST_LINE>u i PM-GretzkyWeds 2ndLd-Writethru   07-16 0505</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Gretzky Weds, 2nd Ld-Writethru,a0486,0517</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gretzky Gets Married</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 4th graf pvs, ``Given his ...'' to ADD that marriage in
Edmonton. Pickup 5th pvs, ``What I ...</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By JEFF BRADLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TORONTO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hockey superstar Wayne Gretzky has more than his
share of titles, but ``Canada's most eligible bachelor'' won't be
among them after today.
   Canadians have been treating Gretzky's marriage to American
actress Janet Jones as their version of a royal wedding, with the
ceremony, the gifts, the ring and even the bride's background
coming under intense scrutiny.
   The 27-year-old Edmonton Oilers star is regarded as a national
treasure, a Mr. Clean who acts as ambassador-without-portfolio for
the sport he loves. He makes an estimated $2.5 million annually.
   Given his squeaky clean stature, it's not surprising his
Edmonton marriage to an actress from Missouri who posed for the
March 1987 issue of Playboy magazine has set the nation abuzz.
   ``What I can't figure out is why he chose to marry a Playboy
bunny when he could have the pick of the crop,'' complained one
letter to the Edmonton Sun.
   But wedding guest Gordie Howe, a hockey hall of famer, described
the bride as ``OK, if you like them young and beautiful,'' and the
Toronto Star heralded ``the royal wedding of a Canadian prince and
his starlet lady.''
   Canadians have learned all about Miss Jones' former flings with
tennis pro Vitas Gerulaitis and actor Bruce Willis, while Gretzky's
former girlfriend, Vickie Moss, was tracked down in Los Angeles for
comment.
   Rumors got so out of hand that Gretzky intervened to assure
reporters he did not pay more than $200,000 for Miss Jones'
three-carat wedding ring; honeymoon plans do not include Lear jets
and private yachts; and guests will drink Canadian champagne, not
Dom Perignon.
   ``We want it to be as first-class as possible, but it is not a
million-dollar wedding like everyone says. We're from sensible
families,'' said Gretzky, who didn't deny buying his bride a
$207,500 Rolls Royce as a wedding gift.
   Miss Jones, 27, is from Bridgeton, Mo., and has appeared in the
films ``American Anthem,'' ``The Flamingo Kid,'' ``A Chorus Line''
and ``Police Academy 5.''
   To accommodate the 700 guests, the Roman Catholic Church waived
its rules to permit the Anglican groom and Methodist bride to wed
in St. Joseph's Basilica, the city's largest church.
   Miss Jones flew in from Los Angeles with her $40,000 wedding
gown. Her sister, Jeannette, is her maid of honor, while former
Edmonton Oiler goalie Ed Mio is best man.
   The couple met in 1982 when Gretzky was a guest on the TV disco
show, Dance Fever, where Miss Jones was a dancer.
   Gretzky began rewriting the record books after entering the
National Hockey League in 1979.
   Until an injury sidelined him part of last season, he won eight
straight Hart Trophies as the league's most valuable player and was
its leading scorer seven times. With Gretzky back for the playoffs,
the Oilers won their fourth Stanley Cup championship in five years.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
