<1ST_LINE>r i AM-India-Murders     07-16 0180</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-India-Murders,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Armed Group Kills Eight in Apparent Revenge Murders</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gang hacked eight bus passengers to
death with sickles Saturday in southern Tamil Nadu state, the
United News of India reported.
   Four people were injured, the news agency said.
   UNI said at least 15 people forced their way onto the bus and
attacked the passengers.
   The killings were believed to be in retaliation for the murder
of a president of a local village council in January, police told
UNI.
   A man identified as Muniyandi, who was accused of planning the
murder of the village leader, and seven of his accomplices were
traveling on the bus when the attack occurred, the news agency said.
   It was not immediately clear if Muniyandi, who uses a single
name, and his associates were among those killed.
   The men were traveling to a local police station, where they
have been required to report periodically since being charged with
the murder.
   The attack occurred near the town of Kumuthi, 300 miles
southwest of the Tamil Nadu state capital, Madras.
</TEXT>
