<1ST_LINE>u i PM-Denmark-Collapse 1stLd-Writethru   07-16 0193</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Denmark-Collapse, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0495,0196</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Dead, Two Missing As Lime Mine Collapses</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with one dead, two missing,
details from police. No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An old lime mine collapsed today,
killing one person and injuring two others, police said. Two others
were missing, including a 1-year-old child, police said.
   At least five persons, all believed to be Danish, were trapped
inside the Timbaek Lime Mine in the northern Jutland peninsula
after the 250-foot ceiling collapsed, a police officer on duty in
Aalborg told The Associated Press. He declined to give his name.
   Rescue workers dug out one person and another was able to crawl
out of the debris, the officer said. Both were were hospitalized
with minor injuries, he said.
   Rescuers found one person dead and searched for the remaining
two under the fallen lime, he said. He said one of the two missing
was a 1-year-old child.
   The cause of the collapse was not known.
   The dismantled mine is 15 miles south of Aalborg. Tourists often
come to the old mine to see a sculpture exhibit and the great
number of bats living there.
</TEXT>
