<HEAD>Leftist Rebels Paralyze Road Traffic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Leftist rebels virtually
paralyzed the nation's roads Friday with threats to attack any
vehicles found on them.
   Almost no traffic moved in the capital city or in the streets of
other major cities. All bus service was suspended.
   Army officials announced increased patrols on major
thoroughfares.
   The clandestine Radio Venceremos broadcast the traffic ban
Thursday and said it would last indefinitely. It said the action
was a protest of what it called President Jose Napoleon Duarte's
repression of the working classes.
   It also said guerrilla commanders have been ordered to increase
sabotage of electric power facilities.
